                        <!-- root element for the items -->
                        <div class="items">

                            
                            	                              <div>
                            		<img src="http://azopera.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/HMS-PINAFORE_MEDIUM_web.jpg" alt="HMS Pinafore this October!" title="HMS Pinafore this October!">
                                <div class="content">
                                    <h2 class="sub">HMS Pinafore this October!</h2>
                                    <p>Set sail on the high seas with Gilbert &amp; Sullivanâ€™s celebrated maritime blockbuster. Beloved for its jaunty tunes, gleefully entertaining story and sassy satire, revel in the first-ever performances of <em>HMS</em> <em>Pinafore. This </em>effervescent production is sure to delight! <em>Â </em><a title="Pinafore TIx" href="http://tickets.azopera.org/single/EventListing.aspx" target="_blank">Click here to buy tickets.</a></p>
                                </div>
                              </div>
                            	                              <div>
                            		<img src="http://azopera.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/BRICK_SPOTLIGHT.jpg" alt="Donate a Brick, Build the Future! " title="Donate a Brick, Build the Future! ">
                                <div class="content">
                                    <h2 class="sub">Donate a Brick, Build the Future! </h2>
                                    <p>Play a major role in Arizona Operaâ€™s foundation for the future by donating a brick to be located in the plaza outside the Opera Center Theater. An engraved brick is a great way to commemorate an occasion or someone special. Bricks start at $250 and come in various sizes. <a href="http://azopera.org/support/donate-a-brick/">Click here</a> to learn more or purchase a brick online.</p>
                                </div>
                              </div>
                            	                              <div>
                            		<img src="http://azopera.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/opera-front_SPOTLIGHT.jpg" alt="Arizona Opera Has a NEW Home!" title="Arizona Opera Has a NEW Home!">
                                <div class="content">
                                    <h2 class="sub">Arizona Opera Has a NEW Home!</h2>
                                    <p>Come and visit us in our new home! On March 25, 2013, Arizona Opera opened a new 28,000 square foot Opera Center at 1636 N. Central Ave in Downtown Phoenix. (NW corner of Central Ave. and McDowell.) This new campus houses our box office, administrative offices, rehearsal space and a black box theater. Click <a href="http://azopera.org/news/2013/arizona-opera-and-city-of-phoenix-join-to-open-5-2m-new-arizona-opera-center/">here</a> for more information.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
                                </div>
                              </div>
                            	                              <div>
                            		<img src="http://azopera.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/13-14_SEASON.png" alt="Announcing the 2013-14 Season  " title="Announcing the 2013-14 Season  ">
                                <div class="content">
                                    <h2 class="sub">Announcing the 2013-14 Season  </h2>
                                    <p>Arizona Operaâ€™s 2013â€“14 season features a new format and new pricesâ€”with five classics that are sure to enthrall and delight! The season is comprised of: <em>HMS Pinafore</em>, <em>The Flying Dutchman </em>(<em>Der fliegende HollÃ¤nder</em>), <em>La BohÃ¨me</em>, <em>La Traviata</em>, and <em>Don Pasquale</em>.<em> </em>To read more about the new season and order an full or mini subscription, <a href="/next-season/">click here</a>.</p>
